  "texts": [
    "For example, it might favor applicants from privileged backgrounds who have had more opportunities to develop strong academic or extracurricular profiles, while disadvantaging those from less privileged backgrounds.",
    "Therefore, while AI algorithms can streamline the admissions process and identify high-achieving candidates, it's crucial to consider how their design and implementation might influence broader educational objectives.",
    "Future versions of these algorithms should aim to balance multiple educational goals, fostering not only excellence but also access and equity (Liu et al., 2023).",
    "On the other hand, ethical considerations surrounding the use of new technologies must be addressed to ensure the acceptability of the evaluation process.",
    "In the case of AI algorithms, evaluations rely on extensive data collection, storage, and analysis, often involving technologies such as facial recognition and body recognition."
